Aeropuertos Espanoles y Navegacion
Aerea, the Spanish airport operator, hired banks to arrange a
500 million-euro ($644 million) loan to refinance debt.  Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA) ,  Banco Santander SA (SAN)  and
La Caixa will organize the transaction, according to a Madrid-
based official at Aena, who asked not be named because of
company policy.  The state-controlled company manages 47 airports in Spain
and had 1.68 billion euros of short-term debt at the end of
2011, according to its  annual report .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid  at 
